comment.narrative:
The targeted numbers where affected by the covid'19 guidelines and thus a limited number  was trained and the remaining will be trained in the second phase.
The over expenditure is arising because the costs of training where  shared across the  3 quarters yet the target was only in quarter 2. Thus an increase in the expenditure as per the quarter one allocated funds. The funds for orientation of youth was not added on the total output cost during integration of the result framework.

The remaining targets will be achieved using the Q3 and Q4 balances on the two trainings of Community local, religious, traditional leaders and youth respectively.;

18 Groups of GYW have been mapped assessed and plans for training them in advocacy are done to be carried out in shifts to prevent participants contract Covid'19  thus a huge budget still attached to the output activities.
The cost reported was fuel and airtime used during mapping.
The targets for groups and cost have not been achieved because the training on advocacy has not been conducted due to covid-19 restriction on movements.;

56 government officials have been reached by L&A on GYW.  The failure to achieve the target is due to the limited activity done under the output. Many activities had been planned starting mid June after the inception meeting but the Covid-19 guideline restricted  70% of government workers from work thus failure to achieve the target.
The cost and targets reported are for District and subcounty inception meetings which are part of out put indicator contributing activities. 
The other activities have been prioritized for the Q3;

The budget variance is that not all male champions conducted the sessions so payments was effected to only those who conducted sessions,
In the quarter 524 (132 Males & 392 females) community members were reached through small group sessions, Dialogues on GBV. From the reported number above 456 were reached by Religious leaders and 68 by Male champions. 

The budget balance is still on She Leads Project Bank Account.;

The target for Q2 was added to the target for Q3 thus making the bigger variance from the quarterly targets. The efforts of having small group sessions in observance of Covid'19 SOPs have increased the sessions by the local leaders and champions thus reaching a number of community members.
The variance in payments is due to payments which where not effected in Q2 and were all paid inQ3.

In the Quarter, we reached 1108 Community members out of which 567 were male and 541 female. ( 475 were reached by male champions while  633 were reached by Religious leaders).;

Under expenditure was due to school re-opening which affected the activity as male champions went back to school and  only religious conducted the activities. 

 This was due to payment of only 40 local leaders, religious leaders and male champions who conducted sessions during the quarter against the target of 130.

Of the 411 community members reached through community sensitization meetings, public debates and Public dialogues 259 were male and 152 female. These were reached out to by the male champions and local religious and community leaders.;
